[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 5/100 path 4/5 answer='Question: Jim spends 2 hours watching TV and then decides to go to bed and reads for half as long. \n\nReasoning: The statement "Jim spends 2 hours watching TV and then decides to go to bed and reads for half as long" means that Jim spends 2 hours watching TV and then decides to go to bed and reads for half as long. \n\nBased on this statement, we can reason:\n\n1. "2 hours" is the amount of time that Jim spends watching TV and then decides to go to bed and reads for half as long.\n\n2. "Read for half as long" means that Jim decides to read for half as long.\n\n3. "Half as long" means that Jim reads for 30 minutes, which means that he reads for 15 minutes.\n\n4. "15 minutes" is the amount of time that Jim reads for.\n\n5. "Read for 15 minutes" means that Jim reads for 30 minutes, which means that he reads for 15 minutes.\n\n6. "30 minutes" is the amount of time that Jim spends reading for 15 minutes.\n\n7. "In 4 weeks" means that Jim spends 4 weeks (2 hours * 4 weeks) reading for 15 minutes (30 minutes).\n\nTherefore, the answer to the question is: Jim spends 15 minutes reading for 30 minutes in 4 weeks, which is 4 hours and 30 minutes.'
