[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 15/100 path 3/5 answer='Question: Three friends spent $20.25 on 3 tickets to the fair. They also spent $4.50 less on food than on the tickets. They also went on 2 different rides which costs $33 for each ride. If they agreed to split all the costs evenly, how much did each of them pay?\n\nReasoning:\n1. The total cost of the fair tickets is $20.25.\n2. The total cost of food is $27.\n3. The total cost of the 2 rides is $33.\n\n4. The fair tickets were purchased for $20.25, which means that each ticket costs $0.90.\n5. The 2 rides were purchased for $33, which means that each ride costs $1.50.\n\nTherefore, the total cost of the fair tickets and 2 rides is $33 + $27 + $1.50 = $55.\n\n6. Since each of the friends agreed to split the cost evenly, each of them should have paid $27 for the fair tickets and $1.50 for each ride.\n\nTherefore, each of the friends should have paid $27 + $1.50 = $42.50 for the fair tickets and $4.50 = $10 for the rides.\n\nThe final answer is $42.50 + $10 = $43.50.'
