[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 19/100 path 1/5 answer='Question: Twenty dozen cups cost $1200 less than the total cost of half a dozen plates sold at $6000 each.\n\nReasoning: The total cost of purchasing each cup is $1200 less than the total cost of half a dozen plates sold at $6000 each.\n\nTo calculate the total cost of buying each cup, we can divide the total cost of the 20 dozen cups by the number of cups we need:\n\n- 20 dozen cups cost $1200 less than the total cost of 16 plates sold at $6000 each\n- 20 dozen cups x 16 plates sold at $6000 each = $12000\n- 20 dozen cups / 16 plates sold at $6000 each = 16 x $12000\n- 16 cups x $12000 = $18000\n- 18000 / 20 = $900\n\nTherefore, the total cost of buying each cup is $900.'
