[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 44/100 path 3/5 answer="Question: Emma can make and upload 72 vlogs per month.\n\nReasoning: Emma was only able to make 18 vlogs for the first week, 21 vlogs for the second week, and 15 vlogs for the third week.\n\nQuestion: How many vlogs should she do to complete the 72 vlogs per month?\n\nReasoning: Emma was only able to make 18 vlogs for the first week, 21 vlogs for the second week, and 15 vlogs for the third week.\n\nQuestion: Natalia sold 48/2 = 24 clips in May, and she sold 48+24 = 72 clips altogether in April and May.\n\nReasoning: Natalia sold 48/2 = 24 clips in May.\nNatalia sold 48+24 = 72 clips altogether in April and May.\n\nQuestion: Weng earns $12 an hour for babysitting. Yesterday, she just did 50 minutes of babysitting.\n\nReasoning: Weng earns 12/60 = $<<12/60=0.2>>0.2 per minute.\nWorking 50 minutes, she earned 0.2 x 50 = $<<0.2*50=10>>10.\n\nQuestion: Betty is saving money for a new wallet which costs $100. Betty has only half of the money she needs.\n\nReasoning: Betty has only 100 / 2 = $<<100/2=50>>50.\nBetty's parents decided"
