[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 62/100 path 2/5 answer='Question: A class of 50 students has various hobbies. 10 like to bake, 5 like to play basketball, and the rest like to either play video games or play music. How many like to play video games if the number that like to play music is twice the number that prefer playing basketball?\n\nReasoning: \n\n1. A class of 50 students has various hobbies, which means that there are 50 students in the class.\n\n2. 10 students prefer to bake, which means that 10 students are in the class.\n\n3. 5 students prefer to play basketball, which means that 5 students are in the class.\n\n4. The number that prefer to play basketball is twice the number that prefer to bake.\n\n5. The number that prefer to play basketball is 2 * 10 = 20 students in the class.\n\n6. Therefore, the number that like to play video games is 20 - 10 = 10 students in the class.\n\nSo, if the number that prefer playing video games is twice the number that prefer playing basketball, the total number of students that prefer playing video games is 10 + 10 = 20 students in the class.'
