[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 4/5 answer='Question: At the local Pick Your Own fruit orchard, you could pick your own peaches for $2.00 per pound, plums were $1.00 per pound and apricots were $3.00 per pound. If Winston picked 6 pounds of peaches, 8 pounds of plums and 6 pounds of apricots, how much did he spend on fruit?\n\nReasoning: Winston spent $26.00 on fruit, which is $2.00 per pound of peaches, $1.00 per pound of plums, and $3.00 per pound of apricots. Multiplying $2.00 by 6, $1.00 by 8, and $3.00 by 6, respectively, yields:\n\n$26.00 x 6 = $144.00\n$144.00 x 8 = $1128.00\n$1128.00 x 6 = $6840.00\n$6840.00 x 6 = $41600.00\n\nTherefore, Winston spent a total of $6840.00 on fruit.'
