[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 68/100 path 1/5 answer='Question: In one year, the number of students on campus doubles at the end of every month. If there are 10 students on campus at the beginning of the year, how many additional students would have joined by the end of May, above and beyond the number of students already on campus at the beginning of the year?\n\nReasoning: In the beginning, there are 10 students on campus. After the first month, the number of students on campus doubles, resulting in 20 students. After the second month, the number of students on campus doubles again, resulting in 30 students. After the third month, the number of students on campus doubles again, resulting in 40 students. So, the total number of students on campus at the end of the first year is 10 + 20 + 30 + 40 = 50 students.\n\nThus, the number of additional students that joined the campus above and beyond the number of students already on campus at the beginning of the year is 50.'
