[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 71/100 path 4/5 answer='Question: George, a grade six teacher, ordered 600 burritos for the sixth-grade class picnic.\n\nNecessary Reasoning:\n1. If there were 50 students at the picnic, and each student was given ten burritos, then George must have ordered 600 burritos.\n\n2. Mr. George eats 20 of them.\n\n3. The remaining 480 burritos are left over.\n\nNecessary Reasoning:\n1. The total number of students at the picnic is 50.\n\n2. Each student is given ten burritos.\n\n3. Mr. George eats 20 of them.\n\n4. The remaining 480 burritos are left over.\n\n5. The number of leftover burritos is 480 - 20 = 460.\n\nCorrect Answer: 460.'
