[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 3/5 answer='Question: Rita hand-picks Junebugs off of her plants every summer. On Monday, she removed 39 Junebugs. On both Tuesday and Wednesday, she removed twice as many Junebugs as she did on Monday. On Thursday, she removed 48 and on Friday, she removed 57.\n\nReasoning: On Monday, Rita removed 39 Junebugs. On both Tuesday and Wednesday, she removed twice as many Junebugs as she did on Monday. Therefore, on Monday, Rita removed 39 Junebugs.\n\nTherefore, on Tuesday and Wednesday, Rita removed 48 Junebugs.\n\nOn Thursday, Rita removed 48 Junebugs.\n\nTherefore, on Friday, Rita removed 57 Junebugs.\n\nTherefore, the average number of Junebugs that Rita removes per day is 48 + 57 = 95 Junebugs.'
