[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 89/100 path 1/5 answer='Question: John decides to get a loan by mortgaging his home.\n\nReasoning: John decides to get a loan by mortgaging his home.\n\n1. Mortgage is a loan in which the borrower agrees to lend money to the lender, with the lender owning the mortgage.\n\n2. The loan is worth 40% of the value of the house, which in this case is $250,000.\n\n3. John uses 60% of that to pay off his debts.\n\n4. 60% of $250,000 is $133,333.33.\n\n5. John gets a loan worth 40% of that, which is $48,666.66.\n\n6. This means that John has a remaining balance of $81,333.33.\n\n7. This additional money is what is referred to as the "leftover" or "surplus" after paying off his debts.'
