[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 89/100 path 2/5 answer="Question: How much money did John have leftover after paying off his debts after mortgaging his home?\n\nReasoning: John's mortgage is a loan worth 40% of the value of his house, which is $250,000.\n\nSince John's loan is 40% of the value of his house, he will have 40% of $250,000 = $125,000.\n\nHe then used 60% of that to pay off his debts, which means he has 40% of $125,000 = $57,500.\n\nTherefore, John had $125,000 leftover after paying off his debts."
