[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 89/100 path 5/5 answer="Question: Jessica has a debt of $10,000 due on her car loan. She has been making payments on time every month for the past 5 years. Her car loan has a fixed interest rate of 8% and a balloon payment of $15,000 at the end of the 6th year. How much money will she have left after paying off the debt at the end of the 6th year?\n\nReasoning:\n- Jessica's car loan is a fixed-interest loan, so her payment amount will be calculated by the fixed interest rate for the loan.\n- The balloon payment of $15,000 is due at the end of the 6th year, so her payment amount will be calculated by the fixed interest rate of 8% for the loan.\n- Jessica has been making payments on time every month for the past 5 years, so her payment amount will be calculated by her on-time payments multiplied by the fixed interest rate of 8%.\n- The fixed interest rate of 8% is calculated based on the original amount of $10,000.\n- Jessica's car loan has a balloon payment of $15,000, so her payment amount will be $15,000 multiplied by the fixed interest rate of 8% (10,000/8%) for a total payment of $137.50.\n- Jessica will have $137.50 left after paying off the debt at the end of the 6th year."
