[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 94/100 path 2/5 answer='Question: The Kennel house keeps 3 German Shepherds and 2 Bulldogs.\n\nIf a German Shepherd consumes 5 kilograms of dog food and a bulldog consumes 3 kilograms of dog food per day, how many kilograms of dog food will they need in a week?\n\nReasoning:\nThe German Shepherd consumes 5 kilograms of dog food per day, which means it takes 15 days to consume 5 kilograms of dog food.\nSimilarly, the bulldog consumes 3 kilograms of dog food per day, which means it takes 7 days to consume 3 kilograms of dog food.\n\nMultiplying the number of days in a week by the amount of dog food needed per day, we get:\n\n15 * 5 = 75 kilograms of dog food\n\nSubtracting the total weight of dog food needed per day (75 kilograms) from the total weight of dog food consumed per day (5 kilograms), we get:\n\n3 * 5 = 15 kilograms of dog food\n\nTherefore, in a week, the German Shepherd and the bulldog will need 15 kilograms of dog food.'
