[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][csqa] sample 29/100 path 5/5 answer="To reason step by step in English, follow the format:\n\n1. Begin with a statement or question.\n2. State the opposite of the statement or question.\n3. Eliminate any implausible options.\n4. Choose the best answer from the remaining options.\n\nFor example:\n\nQuestion: What is happening while he's playing basketball for such a long time?\n\nStatement: He's been playing basketball for so long that he's sweating and pain.\n\nOpposite: He's not sweating and not having fun.\n\nImplausible options:\n1. He's having fun\n2. He's not sweating\n3. He's not playing basketball\n4. He's not knee-injured\n\nChoices:\n1. He's not playing basketball\n2. He's sweating\n3. He's knee-injured\n4. He's not having fun\n\nBest answer: He's not playing basketball.\n\nSimilarly, for the remaining questions:\n\nQuestion: Where might she go if she wanted to go to the desert?\n\nStatement: She wants to go to the desert.\n\nOpposite: She doesn't want to go to the desert.\n\nImplausible options:\n1. She doesn't want to go to the desert\n2. She wants to go to the desert\n3. She doesn't want to go to a populated area\n4. She wants to go to a populated area\n\nChoices:\n1. She wants to go to the desert\n2. She doesn't want to go to a populated area\n3. She doesn't want to go to a populated area\n4."
[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][csqa] sample 29/100 done id=651785ed4f7b0bd2e7ca9f70a42acea5 prediction='A' gold='A' correct=True vote_counts={'A': 2, 'B': 1, 'C': 1, "To reason step by step in English, follow the format:\n\n1. Begin with a statement or question.\n2. State the opposite of the statement or question.\n3. Eliminate any implausible options.\n4. Choose the best answer from the remaining options.\n\nFor example:\n\nQuestion: What is happening while he's playing basketball for such a long time?\n\nStatement: He's been playing basketball for so long that he's sweating and pain.\n\nOpposite: He's not sweating and not having fun.\n\nImplausible options:\n1. He's having fun\n2. He's not sweating\n3. He's not playing basketball\n4. He's not knee-injured\n\nChoices:\n1. He's not playing basketball\n2. He's sweating\n3. He's knee-injured\n4. He's not having fun\n\nBest answer: He's not playing basketball.\n\nSimilarly, for the remaining questions:\n\nQuestion: Where might she go if she wanted to go to the desert?\n\nStatement: She wants to go to the desert.\n\nOpposite: She doesn't want to go to the desert.\n\nImplausible options:\n1. She doesn't want to go to the desert\n2. She wants to go to the desert\n3. She doesn't want to go to a populated area\n4. She wants to go to a populated area\n\nChoices:\n1. She wants to go to the desert\n2. She doesn't want to go to a populated area\n3. She doesn't want to go to a populated area\n4.": 1}
