[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][csqa] sample 73/100 path 3/5 answer='Question: How can you reason step by step in English?\n\nAnswer: To reason step by step in English, follow these steps:\n1. Observe and identify the steps involved in the problem or situation at hand.\n2. Identify the premise of the problem or situation.\n3. Analyze the consequences of the premise.\n4. Determine the best course of action based on the consequences.\n5. Arrive at a conclusion or solution.\n\nExamples:\n1. Observe and identify the steps involved in the problem: The fire department responded to a fire alarm and found smoke coming from the house.\n2. Identify the premise: The fire department is responding to a fire alarm and trying to extinguish the flames.\n3. Analyze the consequences of the premise: The fire department is trying to extinguish the flames, but the smoke is making it difficult to see.\n4. Determine the best course of action based on the consequences: The fire department should use water to extinguish the flames and use a hose to spray the smoke.\n5. Arrive at a conclusion or solution: The fire department will use water to extinguish the flames and spray the smoke with hoses.\n\nRemember to always reason step by step in English.'
