[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 2/3 answer='Question: How many pounds of insects does a flock of ten ducks need per day?\n\nReasoning: The flock of ten ducks eats 3.5 pounds of insects per week.\n\nMultiplying 3.5 by 7 days per week gives us 26.25 pounds of insects per day.\n\nSubtracting 26.25 from 50 pounds of insects per day gives us 29.75 pounds of insects per day.\n\nMultiplying 29.75 by 7 days per week gives us 207.5 pounds of insects per day.\n\nSubtracting 207.5 from 100 pounds of insects per day gives us 87.5 pounds of insects per day.\n\nTherefore, the flock of ten ducks needs 87.5 pounds of insects per day.'
