[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 29/100 path 1/3 answer='Question: Carol spent 4 hours writing a song, half that much time recording it, and 90 minutes editing it. What percentage of her total work time did she spend editing?\n\nReasoning: Carol spent 4 hours writing a song, half that much time recording it, and 90 minutes editing it.\n\nTo calculate the percentage of her total work time spent editing, we need to divide the total work time (4 hours) by the total work time (90 minutes).\n\nThe total work time (90 minutes) is the sum of the hours spent on writing, recording, and editing.\n\nThe total work time (4 hours) is the sum of the hours spent on writing, recording, and editing.\n\nSo, the percentage of her total work time spent editing is:\n\n(4 hours / 90 minutes) * 100 = 40%\n\nTherefore, Carol spent 40% of her total work time editing the song.'
