[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 70/100 path 2/3 answer='Question: While working at the restaurant, each of the forty customers who came into the restaurant gave Rafaela a $20 tip. Julieta received 10% less money in tips than Rafaela. How much money did Julieta and Rafaela receive as tips altogether?\n\nReasoning:\n- While working at the restaurant, each of the forty customers who came into the restaurant gave Rafaela a $20 tip.\n- Julieta received 10% less money in tips than Rafaela.\n- The total amount of tips received by both Rafaela and Julieta is the sum of the amounts received by each of the forty customers who came into the restaurant.\n- The total amount of tips received by Rafaela is 40 * $20 = $100.\n- The total amount of tips received by Julieta is 40 * (10% - 10) = $30.\n- Therefore, the total amount of tips received by Rafaela and Julieta is 100 + 30 = $130.'
