[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 82/100 path 1/3 answer='Question: A jellyfish tank has numerous jellyfish in it. A fifth of the jellyfish are large, and a third of the large jellyfish change color from green to blue under UV light. The other jellyfish are small and always stay blue. When a UV light turned on, 6 jellyfish changed color.\n\nReasoning:\n1. A fifth of the jellyfish are large: This means that there are 50% of the jellyfish in the tank that are large.\n2. A third of the large jellyfish change color from green to blue under UV light: This means that there are 30% of the jellyfish in the tank that change color from green to blue under UV light.\n3. The other jellyfish are small and always stay blue: This means that there are 70% of the jellyfish in the tank that are small and always stay blue.\n\nTherefore, the number of jellyfish in the tank is 50% of the jellyfish that are large and 70% of the jellyfish that are small and always stay blue.'
