[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 95/100 path 1/3 answer='Question: In a family, there are 2 brothers and 3 sisters. All sisters are the same age, which is 16. One of the brothers is 12 years old, which is half the age of the older brother.\n\nReasoning:\n\n1. The total age of all these siblings is:\n\n- 2 brothers: 2 + 2 = 4\n- 3 sisters: 3 + 12 = 15\n- 12 years old brother: 12 + 12 = 24\n\nThe total age of all these siblings is 24.\n\n2. The half-age of the older brother is:\n\n- 12 years old brother: 12 + 12 = 24\n- 16 years old brother: 16 + 12 = 28\n\nThe half-age of the older brother is 12.\n\nTherefore, the total age of all these siblings is 24 + 12 = 36.'
