[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 98/100 path 1/3 answer='Question: The girls are trying to raise money for a carnival. Kim raises $320 more than Alexandra, who raises $430, and Maryam raises $400 more than Sarah, who raises $300. How much money, in dollars, did they all raise in total?\n\nReasoning:\n\n1. Kim raised $320 more than Alexandra:\n\n- Kim raised $320 more than Alexandra by $100.\n- Alexandra raised $430 - $320 = $110.\n- Kim raised $320 + $110 = $430.\n\n2. Maryam raised $400 more than Sarah:\n\n- Maryam raised $400 more than Sarah by $200.\n- Sarah raised $300 - $400 = $100.\n- Maryam raised $400 + $100 = $500.\n\n3. Alexandra and Sarah raised $430 and $300, respectively:\n\n- Alexandra raised $430 by $100.\n- Sarah raised $300 by $200.\n- Alexandra raised $430 + $100 = $530.\n- Sarah raised $300 + $200 = $500.\n\nTherefore, the total amount raised by all three girls was $530 + $500 = $1030.'
