[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][csqa] sample 19/100 path 1/3 answer='Question: What is the best answer to the question "What is the most effective way to manage a person with mental illness who has stopped treatment?"\n\nChoices:\nA. Managed\nB. Dancing\nC. Recovering\nD. Effectively treated\nE. Cause suffering\n\nReasoning:\n1. Commonly known facts: A person with mental illness who has stopped treatment is considered to be in a state of "cured" or "recovered." This means that the person has been cured of the mental illness and is no longer experiencing symptoms.\n2. Implausible choices: Implausible choices include "managed" or "recovering" as the best answer, as these options do not align with the commonly known facts.\n3. Conclusion: The best answer is "effectively treated," as this option aligns with the commonly known facts and provides the best possible outcome for the person with mental illness.'
