[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][csqa] sample 83/100 path 2/3 answer='Question: What is the best answer to the question, "Why might a person be known as a liar?"\n\nChoices:\nA. have no home\nB. false information\nC. hungry\nD. made fun of\nE. brain tumor\n\nReasoning:\n\n1. Compare the options using commonsense knowledge:\n- A. have no home: This option is implausible because a person cannot have a home if they do not live in a house or apartment.\n- False information: This option is implausible because a person cannot have false information if they have not made any.\n- Hungry: This option is implausible because a person cannot be hungry if they have not eaten anything.\n- Made fun of: This option is implausible because a person cannot be made fun of if they have not been made fun of.\n- Brain tumor: This option is implausible because a person cannot have a brain tumor if they do not have a brain.\n\nThus, the best answer is A.\n\nQuestion: What is the best answer to the question, "Where might Sammy go to locate a choker not located in a jewelry box or boutique?"\n\nChoices:\nA. jewelry store\nB. neck\nC. jewlery box\nD. jewelry box\nE. boutique\n\nReasoning:\n\n1. Compare the options using commonsense knowledge:\n- A. jewelry store: This option is implausible because a person cannot be located in a jewelry store if they do not have jewelry.\n- neck: This option is implausible because a person cannot be located in a necklace'
